<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-224-121 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 409 168</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 11 1991 v8 n6 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell preps new message handling service release. (introducesMessage Handling Service 1.5) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell Inc introduces Message Handling Service (MHS) 1.5, aback-end message transport system which handles collection,routing and delivery of messages and files across multiplecomputing environments.andP;  MHS 1.5 will be priced at $100 per E-mailhub for a six-month promotional period to start in Mar 1991.andP;  Thesoftware package will later have a list price of $495 per hub.andO;Novell's MHS 1.5 replaces version 1.1 and Action Technologies'version 1.2 of MHS.andP;  Action Technologies and Novell entered anagreement in which Novell gains ownership of MHS source code,future development of the technology and distribution of MHS forNetWare.andP;  Over 80 electronic mail, facsimile, data base, voicemail and imaging products from about 20 third-party developers arebased on MHS.andP;  Action Technologies Pres Tom White says thecompanies decided on the partnership because of the danger of eachof them backing incompatible versions of MHS.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (Product introduction)Action Technologies Inc. (Licenses).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   Message Handling Service 1.5 (Electronic mail system) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersPartnershipLicensing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>